From f1f18f479c6171676951ed4b5e9af60d5f0ef078 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: srtlab <gomezsteve1379@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:38:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Make the engine resolver a proven superset; delegate
 ModuleSync to it
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Goal: one BCM SEC16 resolution path so ModuleSync can delegate to the engine
without changing the bytes a working BCM produces.

- Extract engParseBcm from ModuleSync.jsx into pure lib/engBcmParse.js (now
  node/vitest-importable; ModuleSync re-exports it so its ~14 importers are
  unaffected). Add engResolveBcmSec16 (the exact secret ModuleSync writes from).
- Equivalence proof (verify-bcm-resolve + a CI vitest) found a real DIVERGENCE:
  the engine's resolveBcmSec16 missed the legacy 2014 (0x00C8/0x00F0) mirror
  that ModuleSync resolves — delegating blind would have bricked 2014 LX BCMs.
- Fix: add the legacy mirror as a CRC-validated candidate in resolveBcmSec16
  (purely additive — only matches the exact 0x8F/FF/FF + valid-CRC signature,
  so no non-legacy BCM is affected). Now ALL AGREE across split/legacy/virgin.
- Delegate ModuleSync's bcm-sec16-to-rfh to resolveBcmSec16 on that proof.

esbuild-validated; equivalence + marry + immo + tabs + provenance all green.
